House Bill 929
By: Representatives Lupton of the 83rd and Lim of the 98th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 2A of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to the Department of Public Health generally, so as to provide for a three-year pilot
3 program for dietetics services for public elementary and secondary school students and
4 patients at federally qualified health centers; to provide for reimbursement; to provide for
5 reporting; to provide for definitions; to provide for termination of the pilot program and
6 automatic repeal of the statute; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and
7 for other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 Article 1 of Chapter 2A of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
11 Department of Public Health generally, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as
12 follows:
13 "31-2A-21.
14 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
15 (1) 'Dietetics' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section 43-11A-3.
